---
title: URL Lifecycle State Diagram
---
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Created: User creates short URL
    
    Created --> Active: Auto-transition
    
    Active --> Active: Destination updated<br/>(short code unchanged)
    Active --> Active: Notes updated
    Active --> Active: Metadata updated
    
    Active --> Paused: User pauses URL
    Paused --> Active: User resumes URL
    
    Active --> Disabled: User disables URL
    Paused --> Disabled: User disables URL
    Disabled --> Active: User re-enables URL
    
    Active --> Expired: TTL reached<br/>(if configured)
    Paused --> Expired: TTL reached
    Expired --> Active: User extends TTL
    
    Active --> Deleted: User deletes URL
    Paused --> Deleted: User deletes URL
    Disabled --> Deleted: User deletes URL
    Expired --> Deleted: Cleanup job runs
    
    Deleted --> [*]: Soft delete<br/>(data retained for analytics)
    
    note right of Active
        • Redirects work normally
        • Analytics recorded
        • Cache populated
    end note
    
    note right of Paused
        • Redirects show "paused" page
        • Analytics still recorded
        • Useful for temporary halt
    end note
    
    note right of Disabled
        • Redirects return 404
        • No analytics recorded
        • URL reserved
    end note
    
    note right of Expired
        • Redirects show "expired" page
        • Can be renewed
    end note
    
    note right of Deleted
        • Soft delete in DB
        • Short code can be reused
        • Historical analytics retained
    end note
